---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<title>Boomerang - Untamed Weapons</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<nav class="nav">
			<div class="container">
				<a href="/" class="logo">UNTAMED</a>
				<div class="nav-links">
					<a href="/rules">Rules</a>
					<a href="/quick-reference">Quick Reference</a>
					<a href="/character">Characters</a>
					<a href="/bestiary">Bestiary</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</nav>

		<main>
			<div class="container">
				<div class="breadcrumb">
					<a href="/character">← Back to Character Creation</a>
				</div>

				<header class="page-header">
					<div class="weapon-icon"><img src="/weapons/Boomerang.png" alt="Boomerang" /></div>
					<h1>Boomerang</h1>
					<p class="subtitle">Tempo Weapon / Read &amp; Return</p>
					<div class="stat-badges">
						<span class="stat-badge">+1 INS</span>
						<span class="stat-badge">+1 DEX</span>
					</div>
				</header>

				<article class="content">
					<section class="weapon-section">
						<h2>Overview</h2>
						<p>The Boomerang is a tempo weapon built on instinct and trajectory reading. A Boomerang user doesn't aim — they read. They feel the angle, the wind, the creature's next move, and throw before the decision is conscious. The throw is only half the technique. The catch is where the fight turns.</p>
						<p>In multi-target encounters, a skilled Boomerang user chains ricochets through packed enemies. Against a single large creature, Split Return lets them hit the body and a called part in the same motion. Neither role requires setup — just position and timing.</p>
					</section>

					<section class="weapon-section">
						<h2>Weapon Attributes</h2>
						<div class="attributes-grid">
							<div class="attribute-card">
								<h3>Tags</h3>
								<ul>
									<li>Ranged (20-60 ft)</li>
									<li>Returning</li>
									<li>Finesse</li>
									<li>Trick</li>
								</ul>
							</div>
							<div class="attribute-card">
								<h3>Attack &amp; Save Stat</h3>
								<p class="formula">Instinct</p>
								<p style="margin-top: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.9rem;">Save DC: 10 + INS mod + proficiency</p>
							</div>
							<div class="attribute-card">
								<h3>Special — Returning</h3>
								<p>After the throw resolves (hit or miss), the Boomerang returns to you unless the Wayback Catch fails. If it falls, retrieving it costs your Move action next turn.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</section>

					<section class="weapon-section highlight">
						<h2>Core Mechanic — Wayback Catch</h2>
						<p>Every throw has two parts: the outbound attack and the returning catch. A clean catch unlocks a return throw as a Fast Action — keeping pressure without spending your Action twice.</p>
						<div class="mechanic-details">
							<h3>The Loop</h3>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Throw (Action, 1 STA):</strong> Make a ranged attack with d20 + INS + proficiency. On hit: deal Throw damage (see table). Regardless of hit or miss: make a Wayback Catch check.</li>
								<li><strong>Wayback Catch Check:</strong> d20 + INS + proficiency vs DC 13. Success (75% at Trained INS): the Boomerang snaps back to your hand — you may make the Return Throw as a Fast Action this turn.</li>
								<li><strong>Return Throw (Fast Action, 1 STA):</strong> Make a second attack against the same target. Deals Return damage (see table). If you moved ≥10 ft before the return throw, add +1 damage die (Ricochet Step, T1).</li>
								<li><strong>Full Loop Payoff:</strong> If the outbound throw AND return throw both hit the same target, you may make a free third throw (0 STA, base throw damage, no bonus die) immediately as part of the same turn.</li>
							</ul>

							<h3>If the Catch Fails</h3>
							<ul>
								<li>The Boomerang lands near the target. No return throw this round.</li>
								<li>Retrieve it as a Move action on your next turn, or use basic movement to reposition and pick it up.</li>
								<li>You can still act normally this turn — the catch check doesn't cost an action.</li>
							</ul>

							<h3>Ricochet (Multi-Target)</h3>
							<p>When the Boomerang hits a target with another creature within 30 ft, you may redirect the outbound throw to ricochet to that creature before returning. Make a second attack roll against the ricochet target at −1 damage die. The Wayback Catch check is made after the final ricochet.</p>
						</div>
					</section>

					<section class="weapon-section">
						<h2>Damage Dice per Tier</h2>
						<table class="damage-table">
							<thead>
								<tr>
									<th>Tier</th>
									<th>Throw</th>
									<th>Return</th>
								</tr>
							</thead>
							<tbody>
								<tr><td>Tier 1</td><td>1d6 + INS</td><td>1d8 + INS</td></tr>
								<tr><td>Tier 2</td><td>1d8 + INS</td><td>2d8 + INS</td></tr>
								<tr><td>Tier 3</td><td>1d10 + INS</td><td>2d10 + INS</td></tr>
								<tr><td>Tier 4</td><td>2d8 + INS</td><td>3d8 + INS</td></tr>
								<tr><td>Tier 5</td><td>2d10 + INS</td><td>3d10 + INS</td></tr>
							</tbody>
						</table>
						<p style="margin-top: 1rem; font-style: italic; color: var(--leaf-green);">The return throw always deals more — catching is the skill expression. Tier upgrades scale both paths; Return scales faster.</p>
					</section>

					<section class="weapon-section">
						<h2>Techniques by Tier</h2>

						<div class="technique-card">
							<div class="technique-header">
								<h3>T1 — Ricochet Step</h3>
								<div class="technique-cost">Passive</div>
							</div>
							<p>You've learned to time your catch with movement — the step back or sidestep adds arc and spin to the return path.</p>
							<p><strong>Effect:</strong> When you make a Return Throw after moving ≥10 ft on the same turn, the return deals <strong>+1 damage die</strong>.</p>
							<p><strong>Interaction:</strong> Works with any return throw, including the return throw from Split Return. Move first, throw, catch, then use the return — the +1 die applies as long as the 10 ft movement was part of the same turn.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="technique-card">
							<div class="technique-header">
								<h3>T2 — Split Return</h3>
								<div class="technique-cost">2 Stamina • Action</div>
							</div>
							<p>Against a large target, you read two contact points — the main body and a vulnerable part — and deliver both in one motion.</p>
							<p><strong>Requirement:</strong> Target must be Large or larger.</p>
							<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Make two separate attack rolls against the same target — one standard body attack and one called shot targeting a specific part (−2 accuracy, as normal for called shots). Both attacks use Return damage dice.</p>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Wayback Catch after Split Return:</strong> Make a single Wayback Catch check for both attacks (not two checks). Success: catch as normal.</li>
								<li><strong>If both attacks hit:</strong> Wayback Catch DC reduced by 2 (DC 11 instead of 13), and you regain 1 Stamina.</li>
							</ul>
							<p><strong>Stamina note:</strong> Split Return costs 2 STA for both attacks. If your Wayback Catch succeeds, you may still make a Return Throw as a Fast Action (1 STA) — total loop cost: 3 STA.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="technique-card">
							<div class="technique-header">
								<h3>T3 — Threaded Arc</h3>
								<div class="technique-cost">Passive</div>
							</div>
							<p>Your throws curve around cover and through gaps that should be impossible.</p>
							<ul>
								<li>Your Throw ignores all cover (half, three-quarters, and full). You may target creatures you cannot directly see as long as you know their approximate location.</li>
								<li>The Wayback Catch DC reduces by 2 permanently (DC 13 → DC 11). Split Return's both-hit bonus stacks (DC 11 → DC 9).</li>
							</ul>
						</div>

						<div class="technique-card">
							<div class="technique-header">
								<h3>T4 — Chain Catch</h3>
								<div class="technique-cost">Passive</div>
							</div>
							<p>You no longer need to stop the loop. A successful return throw opens the door for another.</p>
							<ul>
								<li>After a successful Return Throw that hits, you may attempt another Wayback Catch check (same DC). On success: make another Return Throw as a second Fast Action this turn.</li>
								<li>This chain may repeat once per turn (maximum: Throw → Return → Second Return). Each additional return deals −1 damage die (minimum 1 die).</li>
								<li>Each successful catch in the chain costs 1 STA.</li>
							</ul>
						</div>

						<div class="technique-card">
							<div class="technique-header">
								<h3>T5 — Perfect Read</h3>
								<div class="technique-cost">0 Stamina • Reaction</div>
							</div>
							<p>The throw was already in motion before you decided to make it.</p>
							<p><strong>Trigger:</strong> A creature within 60 ft moves toward you or an ally.</p>
							<p><strong>Effect:</strong> Make a Throw attack against that creature. If it hits, the creature's movement stops for this turn (they may resume movement next turn). The Boomerang returns normally — make your Wayback Catch check as part of the Reaction.</p>
							<p><strong>Limit:</strong> Once per round. Does not consume your Action.</p>
						</div>
					</section>

					<section class="weapon-section playstyle">
						<h2>Weapon Playstyle</h2>
						<div class="playstyle-grid">
							<div class="playstyle-card strengths">
								<h3>Strengths</h3>
								<ul>
									<li>Consistent 2-STA pressure loop — Throw + Return every round</li>
									<li>Multi-target encounter specialist via Ricochet chains</li>
									<li>Split Return contributes part break progress without sacrificing damage</li>
									<li>Skirmisher identity — movement feeds Ricochet Step bonus</li>
									<li>No wind-up or setup required; productive from round 1</li>
								</ul>
							</div>
							<div class="playstyle-card weaknesses">
								<h3>Weaknesses</h3>
								<ul>
									<li>Wayback Catch at 75% — one failed catch per fight costs a return throw</li>
									<li>Single-boss damage ceiling below Bow (no Focus ramp or utility arrows)</li>
									<li>2 STA/round full loop means STA floor hits around R4–R5 without breathing</li>
									<li>Called shots on Split Return still take the −2 accuracy penalty</li>
								</ul>
							</div>
						</div>
					</section>
				</article>
			</div>
		</main>

		<style>
			* { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
			:root {
				--forest-dark: #1a2e1a; --forest-green: #2d5016; --moss-green: #4a7c2f;
				--leaf-green: #6b9d3a; --amber: #d4a257; --earth-brown: #5c4033;
				--cream: #f5f1e8; --text-light: #e8e4d8;
			}
			body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif; background: var(--forest-dark); color: var(--text-light); line-height: 1.7; min-height: 100vh; }
			.container { max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 2rem; }
			.nav { background: var(--forest-green); border-bottom: 2px solid var(--amber); padding: 1rem 0; position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 100; }
			.nav .container { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; max-width: 1200px; }
			.logo { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 900; color: var(--amber); text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.2rem; }
			.nav-links { display: flex; gap: 2rem; }
			.nav-links a { color: var(--cream); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500; transition: color 0.3s; }
			.nav-links a:hover { color: var(--amber); }
			.breadcrumb { padding: 2rem 0 1rem; }
			.breadcrumb a { color: var(--leaf-green); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500; }
			.breadcrumb a:hover { color: var(--amber); }
			.page-header { padding: 2rem 0 3rem; text-align: center; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--amber); margin-bottom: 3rem; }
			.weapon-icon { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
			.weapon-icon img { width: 540px; height: 540px; object-fit: contain; }
			.page-header h1 { font-size: 3rem; color: var(--amber); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
			.subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--leaf-green); font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
			.stat-badges { display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 1rem; }
			.stat-badge { padding: 0.5rem 1rem; background: var(--moss-green); color: var(--amber); border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1rem; }
			.content { padding-bottom: 4rem; }
			.weapon-section { background: var(--forest-green); padding: 2rem; border-radius: 12px; margin-bottom: 2rem; border: 2px solid var(--earth-brown); }
			.weapon-section.highlight { border-color: var(--amber); background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--forest-green) 0%, var(--moss-green) 100%); }
			.weapon-section h2 { color: var(--amber); font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
			.weapon-section h3 { color: var(--leaf-green); font-size: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 1rem; }
			.weapon-section p { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
			.weapon-section ul { margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
			.weapon-section li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
			.attributes-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem; }
			.attribute-card { background: var(--forest-dark); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 12px; border: 2px solid var(--earth-brown); }
			.attribute-card h3 { color: var(--amber); font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
			.attribute-card ul { list-style: none; margin: 0; }
			.attribute-card li { padding-left: 1.5rem; position: relative; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
			.attribute-card li:before { content: "▸"; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--amber); }
			.formula { background: var(--moss-green); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid var(--amber); font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; font-weight: 600; color: var(--amber); text-align: center; }
			.damage-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; background: var(--forest-dark); border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden; }
			.damage-table th, .damage-table td { padding: 1rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--earth-brown); }
			.damage-table th { background: var(--moss-green); color: var(--amber); font-weight: 600; }
			.damage-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
			.technique-card { background: var(--forest-dark); padding: 2rem; border-radius: 12px; border: 2px solid var(--amber); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
			.technique-header { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-bottom: 1rem; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--earth-brown); }
			.technique-header h3 { color: var(--amber); font-size: 1.75rem; margin: 0; }
			.technique-cost { background: var(--moss-green); padding: 0.5rem 1rem; border-radius: 6px; color: var(--amber); font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; }
			.playstyle-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem; }
			.playstyle-card { background: var(--forest-dark); padding: 2rem; border-radius: 12px; border: 2px solid var(--earth-brown); }
			.playstyle-card.strengths { border-color: var(--leaf-green); }
			.playstyle-card.weaknesses { border-color: #c74440; }
			.playstyle-card h3 { font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
			.playstyle-card ul { list-style: none; margin: 0; }
			.playstyle-card li { padding-left: 1.5rem; position: relative; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
			.playstyle-card li:before { content: "▸"; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--amber); }
			@media (max-width: 768px) {
				.nav .container { flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }
				.nav-links { gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; }
				.page-header h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
				.weapon-section { padding: 1.5rem; }
				.technique-header { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 1rem; }
			}
			html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
		</style>
	</body>
</html>
